You will now pay Sh3.39 more on super petrol for the next one month until August 14, latest pump prices review shows. Released over the weekend by the Energy Regulatory Commission, the review shows a dip in the price of Kerosene and Diesel by Sh1.48 and Sh0.35 respectively. The price of petrol in Nairobi will now cost Sh112.20, Kerosene will retail at Sh85.73 while Diesel will sell at Sh103.25. Motorists in Mombasa will purchase petrol at Sh108.90. They will have to part with Sh99.96 and Sh82.94 for Diesel and Kerosene respectively. In Eldoret, a litre of petrol will go for Sh114.05 and diesel Sh105.32, while in Kisumu, petrol will sell at Sh114.12 per litre and diesel at Sh105.39.Nakuru, motorist will pay will pay Sh112.87 for petrol and Sh104.14 for diesel. ERC managing director Pavel Oimeke has attributed the new rates to changes in the average landed cost of imported fuels.The changes have seen the price of Super petrol per ton move up by 5.54 per cent from Sh70,554 in May per tonne to Sh74,460.62 in June. Diesel decreased by 1.11 per cent to Sh68,737 from Sh69,506 in May while Kerosene also decreased by 1.91 per cent from Sh75,142 to Sh73,704 within the review period. “ Over the same period, the mean monthly US dollar to Kenya shilling exchange rate depreciated by 0.14 percent from Sh100.87 in May 2018 to Sh101.01 in June 2018,” Oimeke said in a statement. He noted that the actual pipeline loss factor was calculated at 0.10 percent, less than the standard factor of 0.25 percent.